BT /F1 10 Tf 60 406 Td (infrastructure expansion, public transit allocation, road maintenance planning, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 392 Td (network health monitoring from a single interface. The project uses a graph-based) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 378 Td (representation of Cairo. Nodes represent districts, neighborhoods, and facilities such as) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 364 Td (hospitals, airports, universities, railway stations, and business areas. Edges represent) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 350 Td (roads between these nodes and store distance, capacity, condition, and construction cost.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 330 Td (During the modification phase, the main issue we faced was that the Maintenance DP map did) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 316 Td (not visually behave like the rest of the project maps. It appeared as a separate graph-) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 302 Td (style visualization instead of a real interactive Cairo map. It also needed consistent) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 288 Td (zoom behavior with the other maps. We fixed this by integrating the maintenance result) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 274 Td (into the shared Plotly Mapbox renderer and enabling scroll zoom for all real maps.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 60 246 Td (2. Problem Statement And Objectives) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 224 Td (Urban transportation systems involve many competing decisions. A city may need to find the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 210 Td (fastest route between two points, choose which roads to build, decide how to allocate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 196 Td (public buses, repair damaged roads within a limited budget, and improve traffic signal) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 182 Td (behavior during congestion. These problems cannot all be solved using the same algorithm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 168 Td (because each has a different structure and objective.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 148 Td (- Represent Cairo as a weighted transportation graph using nodes and edges.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 134 Td (- Apply suitable algorithms to real transportation decisions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 120 Td (- Provide an interactive Streamlit interface for non-technical users.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 106 Td (- Visualize decisions on a real Cairo basemap rather than abstract graphs only.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 92 Td (- Support reproducible execution through Docker.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 78 Td (The project focuses on road expansion, shortest-path routing, emergency routing, public) Tj ET
