BT /F2 12 Tf 60 353 Td (4.1 Dijkstra's Algorithm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 335 Td (Dijkstra's algorithm is used to find the shortest or fastest path between two nodes. It is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 321 Td (suitable because all road weights are non-negative. In this project, edge weights may) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 307 Td (represent distance or predicted travel time depending on whether the traffic predictor is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 293 Td (active.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 60 269 Td (4.2 A* Search) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 251 Td (A* Search is used for emergency routing. It improves search efficiency by using a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 237 Td (heuristic based on geographic distance to the destination. This helps emergency vehicles) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 223 Td (find routes while exploring fewer nodes than Dijkstra in many cases.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 60 199 Td (4.3 Kruskal's Minimum Spanning Tree) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 181 Td (Kruskal's algorithm is used for road expansion. Existing roads are treated as already) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 167 Td (connected, and potential roads are sorted by construction cost. A Union-Find structure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 153 Td (prevents cycles. This helps select cost-effective new roads that improve city) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 139 Td (connectivity.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 60 32 Td (Smart City Transportation Network Optimization - Page 2) Tj ET
