BT /F2 12 Tf 60 731 Td (4.4 Dynamic Programming For Bus Allocation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 713 Td (The public transit scheduler uses Dynamic Programming to allocate a limited bus fleet) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 699 Td (across routes. This is better than a simple greedy method because it evaluates many) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 685 Td (allocation combinations and avoids assigning too many buses to a single route.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 60 661 Td (4.5 DP Knapsack For Road Maintenance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 643 Td (The maintenance module converts each existing road into a repair candidate with repair) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 629 Td (cost and repair value. The problem becomes a 0/1 Knapsack problem: choose a subset of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 615 Td (roads to repair without exceeding the budget while maximizing total score gain.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 60 591 Td (4.6 Greedy Signal Optimization) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 573 Td (The greedy signal optimizer models local traffic-light decisions by choosing the action) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 559 Td (with the best immediate benefit. It is fast and useful for real-time demonstrations,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 545 Td (although it may not always produce a city-wide optimal result.) Tj ET
