BT /F1 10 Tf 60 495 Td (The main problem appeared in the Infrastructure page, specifically in the Maintenance DP) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 481 Td (tab. The maintenance optimizer itself worked correctly. For example, with a budget of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 467 Td (2,000 cost-units, the optimizer selected 12 roads, used 1,973 cost-units, and produced a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 453 Td (score gain of +156. However, the visualization did not match the rest of the project.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 433 Td (The rest of the application used real interactive Cairo maps through Plotly Mapbox. Trip) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 419 Td (planning, emergency response, and infrastructure expansion were displayed geographically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 405 Td (using longitude and latitude. In contrast, the maintenance DP visualization appeared more) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 391 Td (like an abstract graph or separate heatmap.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 371 Td (This caused an inconsistent user experience. Users could see real map behavior on other) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 357 Td (pages but not in the maintenance section. It also made the maintenance result harder to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 343 Td (understand because road repair decisions are spatial and should be shown on the actual) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 329 Td (city map.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 309 Td (A second issue was zoom behavior. After the maintenance map was converted into a real map,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 295 Td (the user also needed to zoom in and out of it like the other maps. Then the requirement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 281 Td (expanded: zoom should be enabled consistently across all maps, not only the maintenance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 60 267 Td (map.) Tj ET
